,"why_it_can_fail":"A single composite can mask a weak component; open the Fundamentals tab for the breakdown."},{"label":"Cash conversion","value":0.93,"unit":"\u00d7","status":"good","read":"0.93\u00d7 of profit came in as operating cash (5-yr median) \u2014 well backed.","meaning":"Median of (cash from operations \u00f7 net profit) over the last 5 years.","why_useful":"Profit you can't collect as cash is fragile; >0.8\u00d7 means earnings are real cash, <0.6\u00d7 is an accrual red flag.","why_it_can_fail":"One-off working-capital swings or a capex year can distort a single ratio; the 5-yr median smooths it."},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":0.34,"unit":"\u00d7 D/E","status":"good","read":"Conservatively financed (D/E 0.34\u00d7, interest cover 7.2\u00d7).","meaning":"Latest debt-to-equity and interest coverage (EBIT \u00f7 interest) from the balance sheet.","why_useful":"Low debt and high interest cover let a business survive a downturn; high debt amplifies trouble.","why_it_can_fail":"Off-balance-sheet leases/guarantees aren't captured; a cash-rich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":48.56,"unit":"% YoY","status":"good","read":"Profit up 49% YoY (latest TTM) and accelerating.","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":39.9,"pe_percentile":19.0,"median_pe":48.7,"earnings_yield_pct":2.51,"pb":null,"ev_ebitda":null,"quality_score":95.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":34.3,"peg":1.16,"cheapness":{"status":"good","read":"P/E at the 19-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 cheap vs its own history."},"expectations":"At 39.9\u00d7 earnings for ~34% 5-yr pro